{"text":"Requests are signed with an HMAC-SHA256 signature.","valueDescription":"min: 32 char","more":"- Canonical string format is: {timestamp}\n{HTTP_METHOD}\n{path_with_query}\n{checksum}
        * timestamp → UNIX epoch in milliseconds (sent as X-Timestamp)
        * HTTP_METHOD → request method in uppercase (e.g., POST)
        * path_with_query → URL path + query string (e.g., /webhook/notify?type=invoice)
        * checksum → SHA-256 hex digest of the payload (file field for multipart or body for application/json)"}

